# English only — no ZH translations until further notice

The English UI is still churning. To avoid burning effort on translations
that get rewritten anyway, **do not add or update Chinese (ZH) copy in
[`src/translations.js`](../../src/translations.js)** for new or changed
keys. We'll do a single sweep ZH translation pass once the English copy is
stable.

## What this means in practice

- When introducing a new translation key, add it under the English block
  (`T.en` / first object) only. Do **not** add a matching `T.zh` (or
  `T['zh-TW']`) entry.
- When editing an existing key's English copy, leave the ZH value untouched
  even if it now reads as a stale translation — flagging via lint/diff is
  fine, but don't rewrite the ZH string.
- When deleting a key, remove it from both blocks (cleanup is allowed).

## When to revisit

The user will explicitly lift this restriction with something like
"do the ZH translation pass" or "translations are unfrozen." Until then,
treat ZH as frozen for additions/edits.

## If a fallback is needed

Components consuming missing keys should fall back to English (existing
behavior). If a ZH user hits a new key, they'll see English — that's the
acceptable trade-off for now.
